<br>
Here's what I've uncovered so far. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.landalaska.com/images/arial1.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.landalaska.com/">Blake Island:</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Alaska.<br>
<br>
Island for sale at U.S.$1,800,000.  150 Acres for Sale.<br>
The sale property, 150 acres, is an assemblage of nine contiguous mining claims that comprise 75% of Blake Island's landmass. The remaining 25% is National Forest property with no practical year-round access except across the sale property. Development of the public land is further restricted by the Forest Management Plan, which bars timber sales on Blake Island except in the case of a catastrophic event.  By purchasing 75% of the landmass, the buyer effectively owns 100% of Blake Island's seclusion, privacy, and beauty. <br>
<br>
Zoning and Taxes.<br>
<br>
Because Blake Island is not located within an organized borough, it is not zoned, not assessed, and not subject to real estate taxes.   <br>
**********************************************<br>
<br>
Too small and subject to mainland law. A pity. The price is right. I could probably afford that if I sold up everything.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.webwave.com/snakeisland/images/sm-snake.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.webwave.com/snakeisland/">Rattle Snake Island:</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> Northern California. <br>
<br>
$2,500,000. Fifty three acres.<br>
<br>
Again too small. Also too close to the nearest mainland and it's territory laws. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.privateislandsonline.com/">Private Islands Online.</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
This is more like it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Welcome to Private Islands Online, the Internet's largest directory of private islands for sale. We invite you to browse through our listings of hundreds of available private islands from all over the globe. Whether it's a tropical island washed by the warm Caribbean, or a pine-covered hideaway in a northern lake, you're sure to find a private island for every taste and budget. It's time to turn the dream into reality. Explore the possibilities…<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
A location options box. Let's check out Oceania. Get away from the US and other more controlling regions.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.privateislandsonline.com/titleimages/oceaniaimagemain.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Oceania.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Private islands for sale in Oceania (Australia, New Zealand, and the South Pacific) are some of the most beautiful and remote places on Earth. A South Pacific island paradise… is there anything that more closely resembles Eden? Many of the countries in this region do not permit the outright sale of islands to non-citizens. For this reason, the number of available Pacific islands for sale is quite limited. However, the islands presented here are subject to no such restriction.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Private islands for sale in Oceania have been grouped together by country, for your convenience. To view the extensive collection of listings, select the relevant country from the drop down menu below. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Australia<br>
Fiji<br>
French Polynesia<br>
New Zealand<br>
<br>
Hmmm....? Fiji sounds primitive enough.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.privateislandsonline.com/maps/fijipagemap.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Mavuva Island US$ 3,500,000 43 acres (17.4 ha) <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.privateislandsonline.com/listingimages/mavuvaocfjmain1.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Way too small. I own a forest twice that size.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Private island is situated 23 nautical miles (24.6 km) from the town of Labasa, on the large island of Vanua Levu. Mavuva Island sits on a coral reef, which comes within 400 metres (1300 feet) of the beach. The waters in the protected area within the reef are some 20 metres (66 feet) deep, and host an amazing variety of sea life. The island itself is volcanic in origin, and some lava formations are present. The eastern side has a gradual slope, rising to 110 feet (35 metres). Coconut trees and other vegetation are present, as are fine white sandy beaches. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That's it for Fiji. I'll try another part of Oceania.<br>
<br>
French polynesia is no better. Only a 2.5 acre island. That's probably smaller than a nuclear power plant.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.privateislandsonline.com/listingimages/tuamoturangiroaocfpmain.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Tuamotu Rangiroa Island US$ 1,100,000 2.5 acres (1.01 ha) <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   all private island is situated off the Rangiroa Atoll, 200 metres (660 feet) from the dock at Avatoru. It is well-treed, and has a nice beach. The island includes a villa, 3 bungalows, a caretaker's cottage and a dock. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
Ok, I'll try my own backyard. Futile as I suspect it is.<br>
<br>
Australia.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.privateislandsonline.com/listingimages/longocaubch.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
Long Island. US$1,250,000 8700 acres (3520.77 ha) <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   Private island is immense, so big, in fact, that there are actually 4 countries in the world with a smaller surface area! Situated off the coast of central Queensland between the towns of Mackay and Rockhampton, 20 nautical miles (37 km) from the Great Barrier Reef, Long Island is one of Queensland's largest coastal islands. Open grasslands, forests, and a beautiful coastline characterize the island. There are 4 sandy beaches, one of which is 4 km (2.5 miles) long, and the water temperature remains at 20-22 °C (68-72 °F) all year long. Much of the island is suitable for agriculture, with over 4000 acres (1620 ha) of fertile soil. A 4-bedroom house is present on the island, along with a private airstrip. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Size is perfect. Unfortunately, it lies within Australian waters and is subject to Australian law. No good. <br>
<br>
I'll keep looking.<br>
